entry.title: FREEZING RAIN WARNING, Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 5:13 a.m. EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023

entry.title: Wednesday: Showers. High 7.
entry.summary: Periods of freezing rain mixed with ice pellets changing to rain showers this morning. Risk of a thunderstorm. Rainfall amount 10 mm. Wind east 40 km/h gusting to 60 diminishing to 20 gusting to 40 late this afternoon. High 7. Wind chill minus 8 this morning. UV index 2 or low. Forecast issued 5:30 AM EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023

entry.title: Wednesday night: Rain showers or flurries. Temperature rising to 11 this evening then falling.
entry.summary: Rain showers ending before morning then cloudy with 30 percent chance of flurries. Rainfall amount 5 to 10 mm. Wind east 20 km/h gusting to 40 becoming light late this evening. Wind becoming west 40 gusting to 70 near midnight. Temperature rising to 11 this evening then falling. Forecast issued 5:30 AM EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023
